# Project Structure

- The main application code is in the [app](mdc:app) directory at the root (not under `src`).
- Subdirectories include [dashboard](mdc:app/dashboard), and [tests/[testId]](mdc:app/tests/[testId]) under [app](mdc:app).
- Shared React components are in [components](mdc:components).
- React context is in [context](mdc:context).
- Utility functions are in [utils](mdc:utils).
- Third-party integrations and API clients are in [lib](mdc:lib).
- Static assets are in [public](mdc:public).
- Use shadcn/ui for all UI components.
- Use Supabase client for data fetching and authentication.
- Use Supabase RLS for securing user data.
- Use Stripe via Supabase for paid access.
- Modularize React components.
- Use environment variables for all secrets and API keys.
- Ensure all routes and API endpoints are secure.
- Do **not** use `.mjs` file extension for config files. Use `.js` instead for all config files.